Distribution and ecology:
—Basing on herbarium specimens and literature data (
Gussone 1844
; 
Ferro & Furnari 1970
), 

Centaurea aeolica

occurs in the almost all the volcanic islands and islets of the Aeolian archipelago, except Filicudi (
Fig. 5
). Usually, it is localized in the shrublands as well as in the rupestrian stands.
